{"subjectName":"Business","subjectDescription":"Discover a full suite of online business courses that will allow you to make better business decisions and succeed in today's competitive business world. Our courses provide a rich learning experience that will allow you to develop critical business skills in areas such as business... Read more...","subjectBg":"https://cdn01.alison-static.net/search/header-img/business.jpg","resumeLink":"https://alison.com/resume/courses/3795","title":"How to Design a Performance Management System","totalEnrolled":"-","courseIncludes":["Hours of Learning","CPD Accreditation","Final Assessment"],"headline":"Learn the step by step process for setting up an effective performance management system in this free online course.","description":"Effective performance management is essential for businesses to remain competitive. This free online course will introduce you to a step-by-step process of setting up a companyâ€™s performance management system from scratch. Learn how to set clear goals and conduct data and evidence-based reviews. Young human resource professionals, managers, and business owners will benefit from taking this course. Enrol and start learning today!","courseOutcomes":["-","-","-","-","-","-","-","-"],"courseDescription":"<p>Performance management is an ongoing process and should not be limited to yearly reviews. It requires a system that allows managers to efficiently track, assess, reward, and correct employee performance as part of their day-to-day activities. This free online performance management course will introduce you to a step-by-step process of setting up an effective performance management system. You will see a sample performance review form that you can modify to suit your business needs. Learn how to set up SMART goals for your company based on your company requirements.</p><p>Discover a step-by-step process of defining Key Result Areas for a production manager based on the company goals. Understand the sharing of Key Result Areas with the team member to ensure employee support. Acquire the skills to conduct a performance review, provide performance ratings, and use it to improve the performance of employees. Constructive feedback is supportive feedback given to an individual to help identify solutions to areas of weakness. Study how to provide effective and constructive feedback so that the employee is motivated to improve their performance.</p><p>Performance management manages and improves the contribution of the individual to the organization. Find out how to guide the employee to make an action plan based on the feedback provided on performance, leading to improved performance. After completing this course, you will understand all aspects of the performance management system and apply them in a real-world situation. Young human resource professionals, managers, and business owners who would like to learn how to design a performance management system will find this course beneficial. Enrol today to improve your performance management skills.</p><a href=\"\" class=\"l-but course_btn\"> Start Course Now </a>","certificateDetail":"<p> All Alison courses are free to enrol study and complete. To successfully complete this <span class=\"course-type\"></span> course and become an Alison Graduate, you need to achieve 80% or higher in each course assessment. Once you have completed this <span class=\"course-type\"></span> course, you have the option to acquire an official Diploma, which is a great way to share your achievement with the world. </p><div class=\"l-list l-list--tick\"><h6>Your Alison <span class=\"course-type\"></span> is:</h6><ul><li>Ideal for sharing with potential employers</li><li>Include it in your CV, professional social media profiles and job applications.</li><li>An indication of your commitment to continuously learn, upskill &amp; achieve high results.</li><li>An incentive for you to continue empowering yourself through lifelong learning.</li></ul></di